@{fg shine}To install...@{fg text}



All you have to do is to copy each of the files in this archive to its
belonging directory under "BBS:".

That's all... (Simple isn't it? :)



Configuration :
---------------

There is only one way to configurate this door, and that is through the
Bulls.info icon. If you, from workbench, use information on this icon, you'll
see several different Tooltype strings.

First of all you'll have to configurate where to locate your BullX.TXT-files.
This is done by changing the PATH followed with a "/" to the "BULLETINS_PATH="
tooltype.

Then you'll have to state how many bulletin-lines to be included in the 
bulletin-list. Do not write more than the total amount of Bulletin-lines.

Use the tooltype BULLETIN.x=<name> to declare the bulletin-lines, where "x"
is the line-number and <name> is the name of the Bulletin-Door to be showned.

The tooltype CONFSHOW.x=<parameters> is used to set up in which conference the
Bulletin-Door is to be displayed in. Remember that the "x" is the line-number
to the belonging Bulletin-Door. These parameters is set up like this:


CONFSHOW.x=xxxxxxxxxxxxoxo....etc...etc..

#confnr :  123456789012345...etc...etc..
           000000000111111......etc...

As you can see, each "x" or "o" represent a conference-number. "x" means that
the Bulletin-Door will be displayed in this colume's conference-nr. And "o" 
means that the Bulletin-Door will be suppressed in this conference, and will
not be displayed on the bulletin-list.

2 simple examples to get your minds going crazy :

CONFSHOW.1=xo  - Set up that Bulletin-Door #1 will be showned in Conf #1, but
                 not in Conf #2.

CONFSHOW.1=ox  - Set up that Bulletin-Door #1 will NOT be showned in Conf #1,
                 but will be visible in Conf #2.



Here is an example of how to set up this BULLS.INFO-icon :

-------------------------- Cut Start Here! --------------------------

BULLETINS_PATH=BBS:BULLETINS/
ANTBULLETINS=9
BULLETIN.1=AMFETAMIN
CONFSHOW.1=xxxxxxxxxxxxoxo
BULLETIN.2=Quick-New
CONFSHOW.2=oxxxxxxxxxxxoxo
.
.
.
.


--------------------------- Cut End Here! ---------------------------


Then you'll have to make small bulletin-textfiles. These can include standard
MCI-functions (~) aswell as ordinary text and ANSI-codes.

Each Bulletin-file must have a filename like this "BULLx.TXT", where "x" is the
matching bulletin-line number. And the files must exist in the BULLETINS_PATH-
drawer. Otherwise none of the bulletins will be showned.



Here is an example of how to set up such a "BULLx.TXT"-textfile :

--------------------------------- cut start ---------------------------------

~SS_BBS:Screens/Amfetamin.txt 

---------------------------------  cut end  ---------------------------------

Or you can use : ~CC_BestUl to launch commands etc...



 Megastyle! is not to held responsible if this program should cause any damage
 to your computer or lead to loss of data. It is provided as is, and is being
 installed and used on your own risk. There is no installer-script provided
 together with the UNREGISTERED versions of the Megastyle! productions!


